# DocMind — RAG Document Q&A System

A Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system built from scratch. Ingests documents, chunks and embeds them with a custom TF-IDF vectorizer (no vector DB needed), retrieves relevant passages via cosine similarity, and generates grounded answers using GPT-4o-mini.

## Features
- **Custom TF-IDF vectorizer** — no sklearn, pure NumPy
- **Overlapping text chunking** — sentence-boundary aware, configurable chunk size
- **Cosine similarity search** — in-memory vector index
- **Multi-turn conversation** — maintains context across follow-up questions
- **Source attribution** — every answer cites which document it came from
- **Retrieved chunk inspection** — see exactly which passages informed the answer
- **Works demo-mode** without API key (shows retrieved context)

## Setup

```bash
pip install flask flask-cors numpy
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...      # optional — app works without it
python app.py                      # starts API on :5051
open dashboard.html                # open in browser
```

## Architecture

```
User Query
    │
    ▼
[TF-IDF Embed Query]
    │
    ▼
[Cosine Similarity Search] → Top-K chunks
    │
    ▼
[Build Prompt: system + context + query]
    │
    ▼
[GPT-4o-mini] → Grounded Answer + Source Citations
```

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/ingest` | `{"text": "...", "filename": "notes.txt"}` |
| POST | `/api/query`  | `{"question": "...", "top_k": 4}` |
| GET  | `/api/stats`  | Chunk count, vocab size, history turns |
| POST | `/api/reset`  | Clear conversation history |
| DELETE | `/api/documents` | Clear all indexed documents |

## Key Design Decisions
- **No external vector DB** (Pinecone, Weaviate etc.) — pure NumPy for portability
- **Re-fits vectorizer** on each new document for incremental indexing
- **Overlap chunking** ensures context isn't lost at chunk boundaries
- **Prompt grounding** — system prompt instructs model to cite only provided context